{
  "type": "modeling_module",
  "steps": [

    {
      "section": "intro",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "In this next module, the modeling phase, I will demonstrate what an interaction with a learner looks like."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.75,
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "intro",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "You will see how each interaction follows the same basic structure: the instruction, the learner response, and then reinforcement or error correction."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "intro",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "During this phase, your main job is to watch the flow of each interaction while following along using the flowchart on your content sheet."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "intro",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Let me know when you are ready by saying continue."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "intro"
    },

    {
      "section": "intro_watch",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Before we begin, here is what you should focus on while watching each example: how the instruction is delivered, how the learner responds, when reinforcement is given, what happens if the response is incorrect, and how prompting or correction is used."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "intro_watch",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "You can follow each interaction step-by-step using the flowchart on your content sheet to help understand the process."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "intro_watch",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Let me know if you would like me to repeat these points or continue."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "intro_watch"
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "The first SD is the manding and motivation SD. This SD teaches the learner to ask for something they want to work for. Watch how reinforcement is provided after the learner responds."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "What do you want to work for?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.75,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "... I want to work for the ball."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Awesome! Let's work for the ball today!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Roll",
          "intensity": 0.3,
          "duration": 1.5,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "manding",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "This demonstrates a correct response. Reinforcement is given immediately after the learner responds. Shall we continue, or repeat?"
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "manding"
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "The next SD is the imitative SD. This SD focuses on teaching the learner to copy modeled actions, helping them build foundational skills in attending and motor imitation. The goal is to show an action and have the learner reproduce it."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "... Do this"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Nod",
          "intensity": 1.5,
          "duration": 1.0,
          "repeats": 2,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Nod",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "duration": 0.75,
          "repeats": 3,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "That's nodding your head! Good job nodding your head!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Does the interaction make the purpose and flow of this SD clear? We can either repeat this interaction or continue. What would you like to do?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.5,
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "receptive"
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "The next SD is the receptive SD. This teaches the learner to follow spoken instructions."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "... Shake your head."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "GazeAway",
          "intensity": 2.0,
          "duration": 2,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Let's try that again. Can you shake your head?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Shake",
          "intensity": 2.0,
          "duration": 1,
          "repeats": 2,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Shake",
          "intensity": 2.0,
          "duration": 0.75,
          "repeats": 3,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Nice job shaking your head! Thank you for letting me help you!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.75,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "As you could see, when the learner does not respond, we repeat the instruction and provide assistance."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "receptive_second",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Is it clear what to do when the learner doesn't respond? We can repeat or continue."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "receptive_second"
    },

    {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Next is tacting. This teaches the learner to label or describe things in their environment."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Now, what is in front of me?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Nod",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "duration": 1,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Car"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.6,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Roll",
          "intensity": 0.5,
          "duration": 1,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Good job, that is a car!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "tacting",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Would you like to continue or repeat?"
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "tacting"
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Next is emotion labeling. This teaches the learner to identify and name emotions."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "How do I feel?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "VeryHappy",
          "intensity": 0.75,
          "timing": "after"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Happy!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Great job! I do feel happy right now!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "emotion",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "We have now covered all SDs for this phase. Let me know if you would like to repeat emotion labeling or continue."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "emotion"
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Now we will review error correction. This is used when a learner gives an incorrect response."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Correct responses are quick and accurate. When errors happen, we help the learner try again so they can learn the correct response."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Shake",
          "intensity": 0.25,
          "duration": 1,
          "repeats": 1,
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "After helping the learner, we reinforce correct responses and then continue with easier practice before returning to the original instruction."
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "How do I feel?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "...angry."
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Angry",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Not quite, let's try again. How do I feel? Happy!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "VeryHappy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "after"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Happy?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Good job I do feel happy! Now can you shake your head?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "head",
          "action": "Shake",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "duration": 0.75,
          "repeats": 3,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Good job shaking your head! How do I feel?"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "after"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "kid",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Happy!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 0.8,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "Good job! I do feel happy!"
      },
      "nonverbals": [
        {
          "channel": "face",
          "action": "Happy",
          "intensity": 1.0,
          "timing": "during"
        },
        {
          "channel": "gaze",
          "action": "robot",
          "timing": "during"
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "section": "error_correction",
      "embodiment": "trainer",
      "verbal": {
        "text": "This is the end of the modeling module. If you would like, we can repeat error correction or move on to the rehearsal stage. Please ensure a clear understanding of these practices before moving on. Shall I continue or repeat?"
      },
      "nonverbals": []
    },

    {
      "type": "checkpoint",
      "section": "error_correction"
    },
    {
        "section": "transition_to_rehearsal",
        "embodiment": "trainer",
        "verbal": {
            "text": "You have now seen how each type of interaction works. In the next phase, rehearsal, you will take on the role of the trainer and complete these interactions yourself using the same structure. I will guide you and provide feedback as you go. As soon as you say continue, it will be your job to perform the given SDs in order and follow the procedures described previously. Reference your content sheet as needed to assist you. Let me know when you are ready to begin by saying, continue."
        },
        "nonverbals": []
    },
    {
        "type": "checkpoint",
        "section": "transition_to_rehearsal"
    }

  ]
}